 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>, we must construct an identification from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. By the naturality (<fr:link
href="erct-001V.xml"
title="Naturality of homotopies"
addr="erct-001V"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-001V" /></fr:link>) of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> at the identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H x\colon  f x = x]]></fr:tex>, we have an identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{1_{A}}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Simplifying, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cdot  H x]]></fr:tex>; canceling <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H x]]></fr:tex> on either side, we therefore have the desired identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen H x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
